UID:imagination-practice-fund-year-4-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260428T195559Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260510
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260511
SUMMARY:Deadline: Imagination Practice Fund: Year 4
DESCRIPTION:Final-year practice fund supporting projects that use collectiv
 e imagination to change the world by disrupting extractive or divisive nar
 ratives and/or nurturing equitable and regenerative imaginaries. Looking f
 or work that pushes the boundaries of collective imagination practice\, re
 alises material benefits from it\, creates change inside or outside the sy
 stem\, and contributes to the wider Collective Imagination Practice Commun
 ity via the CIPC Seed Library. Two-stage application: (1) brief initial ap
 plication by 23:59 BST Sunday 10 May 2026\; (2) Community Shortlisting eve
 nts Tuesday 12 May (10:00 to 12:00 BST) and Thursday 14 May (17:00 to 19:0
 0 BST)\; (3) shortlist announced Monday 18 May\; (4) full application from
  shortlisted applicants by 23:59 BST Sunday 7 June 2026\; (5) successful p
 rojects announced Monday 22 June 2026. This year decision-making is shared
  with the community via the shortlisting events. Apply via the initial app
 lication form linked from the Medium post\; questions to hello@imagination
 practice.info.\n\nOrganisation: Collective Imagination Practice Community 
 (Fund Circle\, supported by Joseph Rowntree Foundation)\nLocation: Worldwi
 de\nAward: Up to £3\,000 per project\; approximately 16 collective imagin
 ation projects funded\nDuration: Activities to complete by Autumn 2026\; d
 ocumentation by December 2026\n\nMore: https://medium.com/imagination-prac
 tice/imagination-practice-fund-year-4-e2de01f54da5
URL:https://medium.com/imagination-practice/imagination-practice-fund-year-
 4-e2de01f54da5
LOCATION:Worldwide
END:VEVENT
